{"award_age":70.0,"bio_image":"full\/a3fbd29d24d0fbe6648cd55bca38f555d342fd39.jpg","category":"Physiology or Medicine","country":"France","date_of_birth":"1941-08-02T00:00:00.000Z","date_of_death":null,"gender":"male","image_urls":["http:\/\/upload.wikimedia.org\/wikipedia\/commons\/thumb\/1\/13\/Nobel_Prize_2011-Press_Conference_KI-DSC_7584.jpg\/200px-Nobel_Prize_2011-Press_Conference_KI-DSC_7584.jpg"],"link":"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Jules_A._Hoffmann","mini_bio":"<p><b>Jules A. Hoffmann<\/b> (born 2 August 1941) is a Luxembourg-born French<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Jules_A._Hoffmann#cite_note-1\"><span>[<\/span>1<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> biologist. During his youth, growing up in <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Luxembourg\" title=\"Luxembourg\">Luxembourg<\/a>, he developed a strong interest in insects under the influence of his father, Jos Hoffmann. This eventually resulted in the younger Hoffmann's dedication to the field of biology using insects as model organisms.<sup id=\"cite_ref-nobelprize_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Jules_A._Hoffmann#cite_note-nobelprize-2\"><span>[<\/span>2<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> He currently holds a faculty position at the University of Strasbourg.<sup id=\"cite_ref-www-ibmc.u-strasbg_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Jules_A._Hoffmann#cite_note-www-ibmc.u-strasbg-3\"><span>[<\/span>3<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> He is a research director and member of the board of administrators of the National Center of Scientific Research (<a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/CNRS\" title=\"CNRS\" class=\"mw-redirect\">CNRS<\/a>) in <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Strasbourg\" title=\"Strasbourg\">Strasbourg<\/a>, <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/France\" title=\"France\">France<\/a>. He was elected to the positions of Vice-President (2005-2006) and President (2007-2008) of the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/French_Academy_of_Sciences\" title=\"French Academy of Sciences\">French Academy of Sciences<\/a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-www-ibmc.u-strasbg_3-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Jules_A._Hoffmann#cite_note-www-ibmc.u-strasbg-3\"><span>[<\/span>3<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> Hoffmann and <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Bruce_Beutler\" title=\"Bruce Beutler\">Bruce Beutler<\/a> were jointly awarded a half share of the 2011 <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Nobel_Prize\" title=\"Nobel Prize\">Nobel Prize<\/a> in <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Nobel_Prize_in_Physiology_or_Medicine\" title=\"Nobel Prize in Physiology or Medicine\">Physiology or Medicine<\/a> for \"their discoveries concerning the activation of innate immunity,\".<sup id=\"cite_ref-Nobel_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Jules_A._Hoffmann#cite_note-Nobel-4\"><span>[<\/span>4<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> [More specifically,the work showing increased Drosomycin expression following activation of Toll pathway in microbial infection.]<\/p><p>Hoffmann and Lemaitre discovered the function of the fruit fly <i><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Toll_(gene)\" title=\"Toll (gene)\" class=\"mw-redirect\">Toll<\/a><\/i> gene in <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Innate_immunity\" title=\"Innate immunity\" class=\"mw-redirect\">innate immunity<\/a>. Its mammalian homologs, the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Toll-like_receptor\" title=\"Toll-like receptor\">Toll-like receptors<\/a>, were discovered by Beutler. Toll-like receptors identify constituents of other organisms like fungi and bacteria, and trigger an immune response, explaining, for example, how <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Septic_shock\" title=\"Septic shock\">septic shock<\/a> can be triggered by bacterial remains.<sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Jules_A._Hoffmann#cite_note-5\"><span>[<\/span>5<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Jules_A._Hoffmann#cite_note-6\"><span>[<\/span>6<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Jules_A._Hoffmann#cite_note-7\"><span>[<\/span>7<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><\/p>","name":"Jules A. Hoffmann","place_of_birth":"Echternach","place_of_death":null,"text":"Jules A. Hoffmann ,  born in Luxembourg , Physiology or Medicine, 2011","year":2011.0}